The Balrog, Flame of Udun<br>
The Balrog&#39;s Sword<br>
Whip of Many Thongs<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont">    The objective for the fellowship is this:  Move for the least possible twilight.  I&#39;ve tried the most stealthy approach I can, but I&#39;ve found out that no matter what, the opponent usually can play at least one minion.  This is why I have the armors and weapons.  With A Talent For Not Being Seen, and No Stranger to the shadows on each of your companions (they are all rangers except for the Hobbits), You will be moving for the shadow number +1.  Throw in Deft in Their Movements for a double move, and it will be even less.  I&#39;ve sneaked my way to victory many times with this deck, having won more than lost, and it seems to work very well.  <br>
   The Shadow side is basically a no-brainer.  Play what minions you have, when you have them.  Also, be sure to read the many different combos and texts for the cards, and dont make stupid mistakes.  That is pretty much all, and if you can pull off The Balrog and the Cave Troll at site 5, Kudos to you!  I&#39;ve done it a couple times! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=22707"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=22707" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
